snippet.textDisplay:
My Bipolar heart see's yours and had guessed that your brilliance had come from your being so. Did you know that nearly all the most creative artist and musicians are Bipolar? Google has a great search for it. Honestly I think ALL Bipolar's give their animals voices tee hee, I'm glad you've done it and managed to get it on video and shared it with the rest of us!


The only problem with being Bipolar is that we have many many Brilliant ideas but ONLY IF we had a separate person who we could tell all our ideas to who would follow through with them and only ask us for creative instruction. We would all be millionaires.


I had a rare stroke in 2015 and brain bleed when I came out of it I had a whole story in my mind about a girl from her birth to her death and everything in between. So between being Bipolar and the stroke...yeah. You can go --->> to get a synopsis https://twitter.com/WidowedbyPTSD/status/1060657478747217920


Thank you for putting Sylvester out there and Gibson. I miss Gibson. LIke I said...My Bipolar Heart sees yours. When I'm having a tough time, It's sleep, music and doing "monkey feet" on long pile carpet to ground myself in the physical world. We look forward to more!
Hang in there!

snippet.textDisplay:
A few edge-lords out there think it's cute to say they're bipolar even though they definitely are not and have never been diagnosed(not referring to the cat guy). They seem to think it means you have a few sudden mood swings daily, but it's way more serious than that.
These peoples' entire psyches can swing 180 degrees in the blink of an eye, from happy, outgoing and optimistic to deep depression, very long periods of sleep and dark thoughts of self harm that goth girls would cream over(lol sorry). With that said, all cases are not as extreme and can vary wildly. My ex is bipolar and to say the least it can be scary as fuck for everyone involved. I feel for this guy, especially with all the pets but being as successfulI as he is, I imagine he has at least SOME help, but I could be wrong. So sorry for the long ass post but I felt compelled to explain what I knew about the disorder, because so many people think they know what's up and really do not. Anyone in a position to help this guy should do so IF HE WANTS IT.
